{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"35d7f037-771f-437d-9a9b-cdb52773068b","content":"For a .NET Web API, use the `dotnet new webapi` template. Authentication options include:\n\n| Option | Flag |\n|---|---|\n| None (default) | `--auth None` |\n| Individual accounts | `--auth Individual` |\n| Microsoft identity platform | `--auth SingleOrg` |\n| Windows auth | `--auth Windows` |\n\n**Examples:**\n\n```bash\n# Basic API with JWT bearer auth (Individual)\ndotnet new webapi --auth Individual -o MyApi\n\n# Azure AD / Entra ID auth\ndotnet new webapi --auth SingleOrg --domain yourdomain.com -o MyApi\n```\n\nRun `dotnet new webapi --help` for the full list of options and parameters available for your installed SDK version.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"55d69c4a-fc54-4c11-9e09-a627a4b0cb89","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about web API project templates and authentication options. This is a general knowledge question about .NET (likely, given the repository context with dotnet plugins). I can answer this from my knowledge without needing to look at files.\n\nLet me provide a concise answer about dotnet web API templates and authentication options.","outputTokens":258,"requestId":"4803:8D0D7:106D18:138611:69EABDD5"},"id":"f91a1dab-cb27-4cfd-9353-1cfab023f747","timestamp":"2026-04-24T00:48:29.175Z","parentId":"9f6d90fc-4563-4737-a068-0f228ebc491f"}
